==Greek==

===Noun===
'''ekstasis'''
# Moving beyond oneself
# the flight of the soul from the body
# Originally "standing out from"

====Sartre's usage in Being and Nothingness====
[[being-for-itself]] is seperated from its Self in three successive ekstasis:
# [[Temporality]]: The For-itself [[nihilate]]s the In-itself in the three ways of past, present and future. 
# [[Reflection]]: The For-itself tries to adopt an external point of view on itself
# [[being-for-others]]: The For-itself discovers that it has a Self for-the-other, a Self which is, without ever being able to know or get a hold of

===Related words===
*[[ecstasy]]

